<p>
	&nbsp; &nbsp;As part of the project “Money of our childhood”, the Museum of the History of Money from November 2018 to 
	September 2019 collected money related memories. At the invitation to accept 
	140 people responded to the project. Among them are people of different professions, 
	interests and ages. For many, the project has become a "family", as it involved parents with children. 
	The oldest participant in the project is 88 years old, the youngest is 10 years old.
	<br><br>&nbsp; &nbsp;The main goal of the project is to create a new section on the Museum’s website “Electronic Archive: 
	money of our childhood. " It publishes memories related to money. For example, these are stories about 
	first salary, purchases, piggy banks, monetary reforms, toy money, wins, etc. 
	Thanks to the electronic archive, its readers will be able to learn more about how daily life and the role of money in it have changed over the past 80 years. 
	<br><br>&nbsp; &nbsp;The electronic archive is constantly updated with new memories. 
	We continue to accept stories related to money. We are waiting for your stories to be sent by email 
	<a href="mailto:dengidetstva@gmail.com">dengidetstva@gmail.com</a>, send to mailing address 197046, 
	St. Petersburg, Peter and Paul Fortress, Building 3, letter “G” (marked “Money of our childhood”) 
	or come to the Museum and hand over the handwritten or printed version to the cashier.
</p>

